        "management": "First-line: voriconazole (6mg/kg q12h x2, then 4mg/kg q12h IV; oral 200-300mg q12h). Alternative: isavuconazole, liposomal amphotericin B. TDM for voriconazole (trough 1-5.5). Duration: minimum 6-12 weeks. Surgical resection if isolated cavity/hemoptysis."
